<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Confession" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Confession,</orth> 1) acknowledgment of something to one's disadvantage: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.377.39" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 377</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.432" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 432</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.288" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 37</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>to some c. of his true state,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 9</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) the act of disclosing sins to a priest: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 3, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.164" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 3, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.233" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 22</bibl>.
<lb />3) avowal, acknowledgment: <cit><quote>loves his mistress more than in c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.269" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 269</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he made c. of you, and gave you such a masterly report,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 96</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>